OL,3,CMetal detectorist reunites First World
OL,4,CWar brooch with family
OL,6,F"She was probably out with the cows
OL,7,Fwhen she lost it. I imagine she would
OL,8,Fhave been looking for it for a long
OL,9,Ftime.
OL,11,F"It's a really precious piece of
OL,12,Ffamily history and a great story to
OL,13,Ftell the grandchildren."
OL,15,FDuring the First World War, wives,
OL,16,Fsisters and girlfriends commonly wore
OL,17,Fpin-brooches depicting miniature
OL,18,Fbadges of units in which loved ones
OL,19,Fwere serving in the military.
